article.headline: Cleveland St. 82, Wis.-Milwaukee 59
article.story: MILWAUKEE -- Jeremy Montgomery scored 20 points, including 5 of 7 3-pointers, to help Cleveland State stay undefeated with an 82-59 victory over Wisconsin-Milwaukee on Saturday night. Norris Cole added 14 points and a game-high nine assists for the Vikings (10-0, 2-0 Horizon). Trevon Harmon's 13 points included back-to-back 3-pointers that turned a 15-7 lead into 21-7 with 13:28 left in the first half, burying the Panthers early. Charlie Woods added 10 points. Tony Meier led the Panthers (4-5, 1-1) with 20 points, but no teammate reached double figures. Cleveland State shot 66.7 percent (18 of 27) and 61.5 percent (8 of 13) on 3-pointers to forge a 46-21 halftime lead. Wisconsin-Milwaukee was sunk by its 29.6 percent shooting (16 of 54). Conversely, Cleveland State finished at 63.8 percent (30 of 47) and 63.6 percent on 3-pointers (14 of 22).
